  "texts": [
    "Consider a Stokes-filtered local system of rank 3 with an irregular class consisting of 3 exponents f, g and h, such that the picture looks as follows:",
    "For each of these intervals U i, one has a canonical splitting for the local system V on ((U i) ∂) -, and one also has a canonical splitting on (U ∂) +.",
    "Each splitting corresponds to choosing a basis of the local system on this interval downstairs.",
    "We denote these bases by a, b, c etc., as shown in the picture.",
    "On the other hand, Mochizuki's splitting, denoted ν in the above proof, corresponds to considering the basis a, b ′, c ′′."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}